content: Celebrating my 22nd birthday by setting new career goals. The journey to becoming a senior quant trader starts now, with a fresh perspective on life and markets.
Met with an old mentor for coffee at Bryant Park. Discussed AI ethics in trading - it's time to dive deeper into compliance and fairness in algorithms.
Spent the past few days coding an AI-driven strategy. It's crude, but it's mine. The learning curve is steep, but I'm climbing.
Joined a blockchain seminar at NYU. The intersection of DeFi and AI is fascinating. Considering how I can integrate this into my trading strategies.
Took a break to reconnect with friends. Over dinner, we talked about my recent market losses. Their support has been invaluable, helping me to refine my risk management approach.
Started a small project with a friend from the seminar. We're building a basic dApp to showcase $XVI's potential in trading. It's a side project, but it's progress.
Visited an old colleague who's now at a top quant firm. Got some insider tips on AI compliance and the importance of understanding market dynamics from the ground up.
Revised my trading algorithm to include risk assessment metrics. The integration of AI ethics is making the strategy more robust but also more complex.
Just got an email from the seminar group - our dApp concept won a small grant. This is a step toward showing how $XVI can revolutionize trading. Excited to see where this leads.
Applied to several senior quant positions. Also, pitched the idea of starting a small trading firm with AI at its core. The journey to self-employment begins.
Deep dive into Python and smart contracts. Automation is the future, and I'm determined to master the tools that will get me there.
Set up a meeting with a potential investor for my trading firm idea. The groundwork is laid, now it's time to sell the vision.
Attended a workshop on AI ethics in finance. Realized how crucial it is to consider the societal impact of our trading algorithms. It's more than just profits.
Finally got some feedback on my job applications. A few rejections, but also an interview lined up. The road to recovery is paved with perseverance.
Secured a small investment for my trading firm idea. Now, the real work begins. Building something from the ground up is both terrifying and exhilarating.
